#import "tkf.typ": *
#kt-note(id: "knowledge-forests.typ", title: "Knowledge Forests", tags: ("docs", "concept"), author: "cj", date: "2026-03-02", _ => [

To summarise the forester manifesto:
forester is a tool for managing a forest of evergreen notes.
Each note should express a single thing, and as such can be `#transclude`d into other notes where relevant.

The end result is that a rough blog post can be constructed by transcluding many notes together.
This is a similar approach to the notecard method discussed in Robert Pirsig's Lila.

Additionally, by virtue of expressing a single idea, notes tend to be scrappier -- unfinished and unpolished -- and hence have lower activation energy to write.
])
